item.description:
September 2004<br/><br/>In the June 2004 issue of MSDN®Magazine, I described a class called ShowTime that you can use to do simple performance monitoring for your app.  ShowTime uses its constructor/destructor to record the start/stop times of its existence so you can instantiate it in a block of code like so:


{
   ShowTime st(_T("Total time is:"));
   // some lengthy operation
}
.
